<plot>Woody Woodpecker encounters a leprechaun woodpecker and the little fellow with an Irish-brogue gives him three wishes. The first wish gets Woody into much trouble and several escapades with the police; his second wish gets him back home again. Woody uses his third and final wish wishing that the leprechaun would go to blazes, which he does in a grand finale fit for Dante's Inferno. Woody should have asked the little fellow the reason why a leprechaun would choose to be a woodpecker?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?240182</url></doc>
